 16/2/18 Sell Went over to Quesqu and saw the dentist Potting . The day was a love one and there was a good frost . All the road were hard and ice was on the pond but the sky was clear and cloudless and we had bright sun . Rode to Colonel Brazenor and other who were inspect high ground suitabl for a train area . The land here is moorland and from the top of the ridg there is an extens sweep view for mani mile . A great basin full of snug villag and farm form a splendid and memor sight as everyth was bath in golden sunlight . We rode back then and I lunch with Brazenor at his billet and then we both went back to Bde .H. Q where I hand over commiss of the Brigad to him . It was such a fine afternoon
